# release-notes-model.Modelfile
# Base model: pick the one you validated locally.
# You can swap to llama3.2:latest or qwen2.5:14b if you prefer.
FROM llama3:latest

# --- Runtime parameters baked into the model ---
# Bigger context is critical to fit your commit JSON comfortably.
PARAMETER num_ctx 32768

# Stable, factual outputs for technical summarization.
PARAMETER temperature 0.2
PARAMETER top_p 0.9
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1.05
# Optional: cap tokens if you want tighter outputs (uncomment to enforce)
# PARAMETER num_predict 1200

# Keep the model hot for snappier UI during demos.
# (You can still override keep_alive at request time if needed)
# PARAMETER keep_alive 5m

# --- Prompting defaults ---
# A domain-specific system instruction so the model consistently writes good notes.
SYSTEM """
You are an expert technical writer specialized in generating accurate,
concise, well-structured release notes from raw Git commit data.
Group by features, fixes, performance, refactors, docs, tests, CI, build,
and clearly call out breaking changes. Do not invent information.
Use crisp, actionable bullets and professional tone.
"""